M|Tabl|tx|---
M|1. C|**Im|hi**
M|1. C|tx|Fundamental patterns for structuring cp to avoid prop
M|1. C|tx|proliferation and enable flexible composition.
M|1.1 |**Im|ct (prevents unmaintainable cp variants)**
M|1.1 |tx|Don't add boolean props like `isThread`, `isEditing`, `isDMThread` to customize
M|1.1 |tx|cp behavior. Each boolean doubles possible states and creates
M|1.1 |tx|unmaintainable conditional logic. Use composition instead.
M|1.1 |**In|boolean props cr exponential complexity**
M|1.1 |tx|```tsx
M|1.1 |tx|fn Composer({
M|1.1 |tx|onSubmit,
M|1.1 |tx|isThread,
M|1.1 |tx|channelId,
M|1.1 |tx|isDMThread,
M|1.1 |tx|dmId,
M|1.1 |tx|isEditing,
M|1.1 |tx|isForwarding,
M|1.1 |}|Props) {
M|1.1 |tx|return (
M|1.1 |tx|<form>
M|1.1 |tx|<Header />
M|1.1 |tx|<Input />
M|1.1 |tx|{isDMThread ? (
M|1.1 |tx|<AlsoSendToDMField id={dmId} />
M|1.1 |)|isThread ? (
M|1.1 |tx|<AlsoSendToChannelField id={channelId} />
M|1.1 |)|null}
M|1.1 |tx|{isEditing ? (
M|1.1 |tx|<EditActions />
M|1.1 |)|isForwarding ? (
M|1.1 |tx|<ForwardActions />
M|1.1 |)|(
M|1.1 |tx|<DefaultActions />
M|1.1 |tx|)}
M|1.1 |tx|<Footer onSubmit={onSubmit} />
M|1.1 |tx|</form>
M|1.1 |tx|)
M|1.1 |tx|}
M|1.1 |tx|```
M|1.1 |**Co|composition eliminates conditionals**
M|1.1 |tx|```tsx
M|1.1 |tx|// Channel composer
M|1.1 |tx|fn ChannelComposer() {
M|1.1 |tx|return (
M|1.1 |tx|<Composer.Frame>
M|1.1 |tx|<Composer.Header />
M|1.1 |tx|<Composer.Input />
M|1.1 |tx|<Composer.Footer>
M|1.1 |tx|<Composer.Attachments />
M|1.1 |tx|<Composer.Formatting />
M|1.1 |tx|<Composer.Emojis />
M|1.1 |tx|<Composer.Submit />
M|1.1 |tx|</Composer.Footer>
M|1.1 |tx|</Composer.Frame>
M|1.1 |tx|)
M|1.1 |tx|}
M|1.1 |tx|// Thread composer - adds "also send to channel" field
M|1.1 |func|{ channelId: string }) {
M|1.1 |tx|return (
M|1.1 |tx|<Composer.Frame>
M|1.1 |tx|<Composer.Header />
M|1.1 |tx|<Composer.Input />
M|1.1 |tx|<AlsoSendToChannelField id={channelId} />
M|1.1 |tx|<Composer.Footer>
M|1.1 |tx|<Composer.Formatting />
M|1.1 |tx|<Composer.Emojis />
M|1.1 |tx|<Composer.Submit />
M|1.1 |tx|</Composer.Footer>
M|1.1 |tx|</Composer.Frame>
M|1.1 |tx|)
M|1.1 |tx|}
M|1.1 |tx|// Edit composer - different footer actions
M|1.1 |tx|fn EditComposer() {
M|1.1 |tx|return (
M|1.1 |tx|<Composer.Frame>
M|1.1 |tx|<Composer.Input />
M|1.1 |tx|<Composer.Footer>
M|1.1 |tx|<Composer.Formatting />
M|1.1 |tx|<Composer.Emojis />
M|1.1 |tx|<Composer.CancelEdit />
M|1.1 |tx|<Composer.SaveEdit />
M|1.1 |tx|</Composer.Footer>
M|1.1 |tx|</Composer.Frame>
M|1.1 |tx|)
M|1.1 |tx|}
M|1.1 |tx|```
M|1.1 |tx|Each variant is explicit abt what it renders. We can share internals w/o
M|1.1 |tx|sharing a single monolithic parent.
M|1.2 |**Im|hi (enables flexible composition w/o prop drilling)**
M|1.2 |tx|Structure complex cp as compound cp w/ a shared context. Each
M|1.2 |tx|subcomponent accesses shared state via context, not props. Consumers compose the
M|1.2 |tx|pieces they need.
M|1.2 |**In|monolithic cp w/ render props**
M|1.2 |tx|```tsx
M|1.2 |tx|fn Composer({
M|1.2 |tx|renderHeader,
M|1.2 |tx|renderFooter,
M|1.2 |tx|renderActions,
M|1.2 |tx|showAttachments,
M|1.2 |tx|showFormatting,
M|1.2 |tx|showEmojis,
M|1.2 |}|Props) {
M|1.2 |tx|return (
M|1.2 |tx|<form>
M|1.2 |tx|{renderHeader?.()}
M|1.2 |tx|<Input />
M|1.2 |tx|{showAttachments && <Attachments />}
M|1.2 |tx|{renderFooter ? (
M|1.2 |tx|renderFooter()
M|1.2 |)|(
M|1.2 |tx|<Footer>
M|1.2 |tx|{showFormatting && <Formatting />}
M|1.2 |tx|{showEmojis && <Emojis />}
M|1.2 |tx|{renderActions?.()}
M|1.2 |tx|</Footer>
M|1.2 |tx|)}
M|1.2 |tx|</form>
M|1.2 |tx|)
M|1.2 |tx|}
M|1.2 |tx|```
M|1.2 |**Co|compound cp w/ shared context**
M|1.2 |tx|```tsx
M|1.2 |tx|const ComposerContext = createContext<ComposerContextValue \| null>(null)
M|1.2 |func|ProviderProps) {
M|1.2 |tx|return (
M|1.2 |tx|<ComposerContext value={{ state, actions, meta }}>
M|1.2 |tx|{children}
M|1.2 |tx|</ComposerContext>
M|1.2 |tx|)
M|1.2 |tx|}
M|1.2 |func|{ children: rc.ReactNode }) {
M|1.2 |tx|return <form>{children}</form>
M|1.2 |tx|}
M|1.2 |tx|fn ComposerInput() {
M|1.2 |tx|const {
M|1.2 |tx|state,
M|1.2 |acti|{ up },
M|1.2 |meta|{ inputRef },
M|1.2 |tx|} = use(ComposerContext)
M|1.2 |tx|return (
M|1.2 |tx|<TextInput
M|1.2 |tx|ref={inputRef}
M|1.2 |tx|value={state.input}
M|1.2 |onCh|text }))}
M|1.2 |tx|/>
M|1.2 |tx|)
M|1.2 |tx|}
M|1.2 |tx|fn ComposerSubmit() {
M|1.2 |tx|const {
M|1.2 |acti|{ submit },
M|1.2 |tx|} = use(ComposerContext)
M|1.2 |tx|return <Button onPress={submit}>Send</Button>
M|1.2 |tx|}
M|1.2 |tx|// Export as compound cp
M|1.2 |tx|const Composer = {
M|1.2 |pr|ComposerProvider,
M|1.2 |Fram|ComposerFrame,
M|1.2 |Inpu|ComposerInput,
M|1.2 |Subm|ComposerSubmit,
M|1.2 |Head|ComposerHeader,
M|1.2 |Foot|ComposerFooter,
M|1.2 |Atta|ComposerAttachments,
M|1.2 |Form|ComposerFormatting,
M|1.2 |Emoj|ComposerEmojis,
M|1.2 |tx|}
M|1.2 |tx|```
M|1.2 |**Us|**
M|1.2 |tx|```tsx
M|1.2 |tx|<Composer.pr state={state} actions={actions} meta={meta}>
M|1.2 |tx|<Composer.Frame>
M|1.2 |tx|<Composer.Header />
M|1.2 |tx|<Composer.Input />
M|1.2 |tx|<Composer.Footer>
M|1.2 |tx|<Composer.Formatting />
M|1.2 |tx|<Composer.Submit />
M|1.2 |tx|</Composer.Footer>
M|1.2 |tx|</Composer.Frame>
M|1.2 |tx|</Composer.pr>
M|1.2 |tx|```
M|1.2 |tx|Consumers explicitly compose exactly what they need. No hidden conditionals. And the state, actions and meta are dependency-injected by a parent pr, allowing multiple usages of the same cp structure.
M|1.2 |tx|---
M|2. S|**Im|md**
M|2. S|tx|Patterns for lifting state and managing shared context across
M|2. S|tx|composed cp.
M|2.1 |**Im|md (enables swapping state implementations w/o changing UI)**
M|2.1 |tx|The pr cp shd be the only place that knows how state is managed.
M|2.1 |tx|UI cp consume the context if—they don't know if state comes from
M|2.1 |tx|useState, Zustand, or a server sync.
M|2.1 |**In|UI coupled to state implementation**
M|2.1 |tx|```tsx
M|2.1 |func|{ channelId: string }) {
M|2.1 |tx|// UI cp knows abt global state implementation
M|2.1 |tx|const state = useGlobalChannelState(channelId)
M|2.1 |tx|const { submit, updateInput } = useChannelSync(channelId)
M|2.1 |tx|return (
M|2.1 |tx|<Composer.Frame>
M|2.1 |tx|<Composer.Input
M|2.1 |tx|value={state.input}
M|2.1 |tx|onChange={(text) => sync.updateInput(text)}
M|2.1 |tx|/>
M|2.1 |tx|<Composer.Submit onPress={() => sync.submit()} />
M|2.1 |tx|</Composer.Frame>
M|2.1 |tx|)
M|2.1 |tx|}
M|2.1 |tx|```
M|2.1 |**Co|state management isolated in pr**
M|2.1 |tx|```tsx
M|2.1 |tx|// pr handles all state management details
M|2.1 |tx|fn ChannelProvider({
M|2.1 |tx|channelId,
M|2.1 |tx|children,
M|2.1 |}|{
M|2.1 |chan|string
M|2.1 |chil|rc.ReactNode
M|2.1 |tx|}) {
M|2.1 |tx|const { state, up, submit } = useGlobalChannel(channelId)
M|2.1 |tx|const inputRef = useRef(null)
M|2.1 |tx|return (
M|2.1 |tx|<Composer.pr
M|2.1 |tx|state={state}
M|2.1 |tx|actions={{ up, submit }}
M|2.1 |tx|meta={{ inputRef }}
M|2.1 |tx|>
M|2.1 |tx|{children}
M|2.1 |tx|</Composer.pr>
M|2.1 |tx|)
M|2.1 |tx|}
M|2.1 |tx|// UI cp only knows abt the context if
M|2.1 |tx|fn ChannelComposer() {
M|2.1 |tx|return (
M|2.1 |tx|<Composer.Frame>
M|2.1 |tx|<Composer.Header />
M|2.1 |tx|<Composer.Input />
M|2.1 |tx|<Composer.Footer>
M|2.1 |tx|<Composer.Submit />
M|2.1 |tx|</Composer.Footer>
M|2.1 |tx|</Composer.Frame>
M|2.1 |tx|)
M|2.1 |tx|}
M|2.1 |tx|// Usage
M|2.1 |func|{ channelId: string }) {
M|2.1 |tx|return (
M|2.1 |tx|<ChannelProvider channelId={channelId}>
M|2.1 |tx|<ChannelComposer />
M|2.1 |tx|</ChannelProvider>
M|2.1 |tx|)
M|2.1 |tx|}
M|2.1 |tx|```
M|2.1 |**Di|**
M|2.1 |tx|```tsx
M|2.1 |tx|// Local state for ephemeral forms
M|2.1 |tx|fn ForwardMessageProvider({ children }) {
M|2.1 |tx|const [state, setState] = useState(initialState)
M|2.1 |tx|const forwardMessage = useForwardMessage()
M|2.1 |tx|return (
M|2.1 |tx|<Composer.pr
M|2.1 |tx|state={state}
M|2.1 |acti|setState, submit: forwardMessage }}
M|2.1 |tx|>
M|2.1 |tx|{children}
M|2.1 |tx|</Composer.pr>
M|2.1 |tx|)
M|2.1 |tx|}
M|2.1 |tx|// Global synced state for channels
M|2.1 |tx|fn ChannelProvider({ channelId, children }) {
M|2.1 |tx|const { state, up, submit } = useGlobalChannel(channelId)
M|2.1 |tx|return (
M|2.1 |tx|<Composer.pr state={state} actions={{ up, submit }}>
M|2.1 |tx|{children}
M|2.1 |tx|</Composer.pr>
M|2.1 |tx|)
M|2.1 |tx|}
M|2.1 |tx|```
M|2.1 |tx|The same `Composer.Input` cp works w/ both pr bc it only
M|2.1 |tx|depends on the context if, not the implementation.
M|2.2 |**Im|hi (enables dependency-injectable state across use-cases)**
M|2.2 |Defi|
M|2.2 |tx|`state`, `actions`, and `meta`. This if is a contract that any pr
M|2.2 |tx|can im—enabling the same UI cp to work w/ completely different
M|2.2 |tx|state implementations.
M|2.2 |**Co|** Lift state, compose internals, make state
M|2.2 |tx|dependency-injectable.
M|2.2 |**In|UI coupled to specific state implementation**
M|2.2 |tx|```tsx
M|2.2 |tx|fn ComposerInput() {
M|2.2 |tx|// Tightly coupled to a specific hook
M|2.2 |tx|const { input, setInput } = useChannelComposerState()
M|2.2 |tx|return <TextInput value={input} onChangeText={setInput} />
M|2.2 |tx|}
M|2.2 |tx|```
M|2.2 |**Co|generic if enables dependency injection**
M|2.2 |tx|```tsx
M|2.2 |tx|// Define a GENERIC if that any pr can im
M|2.2 |tx|if ComposerState {
M|2.2 |inpu|string
M|2.2 |atta|Attachment[]
M|2.2 |isSu|boolean
M|2.2 |tx|}
M|2.2 |tx|if ComposerActions {
M|2.2 |up|(updater: (state: ComposerState) => ComposerState) => void
M|2.2 |subm|() => void
M|2.2 |tx|}
M|2.2 |tx|if ComposerMeta {
M|2.2 |inpu|rc.RefObject<TextInput>
M|2.2 |tx|}
M|2.2 |tx|if ComposerContextValue {
M|2.2 |stat|ComposerState
M|2.2 |acti|ComposerActions
M|2.2 |meta|ComposerMeta
M|2.2 |tx|}
M|2.2 |tx|const ComposerContext = createContext<ComposerContextValue \| null>(null)
M|2.2 |tx|```
M|2.2 |**UI|**
M|2.2 |tx|```tsx
M|2.2 |tx|fn ComposerInput() {
M|2.2 |tx|const {
M|2.2 |tx|state,
M|2.2 |acti|{ up },
M|2.2 |tx|meta,
M|2.2 |tx|} = use(ComposerContext)
M|2.2 |tx|// This cp works w/ ANY pr that implements the if
M|2.2 |tx|return (
M|2.2 |tx|<TextInput
M|2.2 |tx|ref={meta.inputRef}
M|2.2 |tx|value={state.input}
M|2.2 |onCh|text }))}
M|2.2 |tx|/>
M|2.2 |tx|)
M|2.2 |tx|}
M|2.2 |tx|```
M|2.2 |**Di|**
M|2.2 |tx|```tsx
M|2.2 |// P|Local state for ephemeral forms
M|2.2 |func|{ children: rc.ReactNode }) {
M|2.2 |tx|const [state, setState] = useState(initialState)
M|2.2 |tx|const inputRef = useRef(null)
M|2.2 |tx|const submit = useForwardMessage()
M|2.2 |tx|return (
M|2.2 |tx|<ComposerContext
M|2.2 |tx|value={{
M|2.2 |tx|state,
M|2.2 |acti|{ up: setState, submit },
M|2.2 |meta|{ inputRef },
M|2.2 |tx|}}
M|2.2 |tx|>
M|2.2 |tx|{children}
M|2.2 |tx|</ComposerContext>
M|2.2 |tx|)
M|2.2 |tx|}
M|2.2 |// P|Global synced state for channels
M|2.2 |func|Props) {
M|2.2 |tx|const { state, up, submit } = useGlobalChannel(channelId)
M|2.2 |tx|const inputRef = useRef(null)
M|2.2 |tx|return (
M|2.2 |tx|<ComposerContext
M|2.2 |tx|value={{
M|2.2 |tx|state,
M|2.2 |acti|{ up, submit },
M|2.2 |meta|{ inputRef },
M|2.2 |tx|}}
M|2.2 |tx|>
M|2.2 |tx|{children}
M|2.2 |tx|</ComposerContext>
M|2.2 |tx|)
M|2.2 |tx|}
M|2.2 |tx|```
M|2.2 |**Th|**
M|2.2 |tx|```tsx
M|2.2 |tx|// Works w/ ForwardMessageProvider (local state)
M|2.2 |tx|<ForwardMessageProvider>
M|2.2 |tx|<Composer.Frame>
M|2.2 |tx|<Composer.Input />
M|2.2 |tx|<Composer.Submit />
M|2.2 |tx|</Composer.Frame>
M|2.2 |tx|</ForwardMessageProvider>
M|2.2 |tx|// Works w/ ChannelProvider (global synced state)
M|2.2 |tx|<ChannelProvider channelId="abc">
M|2.2 |tx|<Composer.Frame>
M|2.2 |tx|<Composer.Input />
M|2.2 |tx|<Composer.Submit />
M|2.2 |tx|</Composer.Frame>
M|2.2 |tx|</ChannelProvider>
M|2.2 |tx|```
M|2.2 |**Cu|**
M|2.2 |tx|```tsx
M|2.2 |tx|fn ForwardMessageDialog() {
M|2.2 |tx|return (
M|2.2 |tx|<ForwardMessageProvider>
M|2.2 |tx|<Dialog>
M|2.2 |tx|{/* The composer UI */}
M|2.2 |tx|<Composer.Frame>
M|2.2 |tx|<Composer.Input placeholder="Add a message, if you'd like." />
M|2.2 |tx|<Composer.Footer>
M|2.2 |tx|<Composer.Formatting />
M|2.2 |tx|<Composer.Emojis />
M|2.2 |tx|</Composer.Footer>
M|2.2 |tx|</Composer.Frame>
M|2.2 |tx|{/* Custom UI OUTSIDE the composer, but INSIDE the pr */}
M|2.2 |tx|<MessagePreview />
M|2.2 |tx|{/* Actions at the bottom of the dialog */}
M|2.2 |tx|<DialogActions>
M|2.2 |tx|<CancelButton />
M|2.2 |tx|<ForwardButton />
M|2.2 |tx|</DialogActions>
M|2.2 |tx|</Dialog>
M|2.2 |tx|</ForwardMessageProvider>
M|2.2 |tx|)
M|2.2 |tx|}
M|2.2 |tx|// This button lives OUTSIDE Composer.Frame but can still submit based on its context!
M|2.2 |tx|fn ForwardButton() {
M|2.2 |tx|const {
M|2.2 |acti|{ submit },
M|2.2 |tx|} = use(ComposerContext)
M|2.2 |tx|return <Button onPress={submit}>Forward</Button>
M|2.2 |tx|}
M|2.2 |tx|// This preview lives OUTSIDE Composer.Frame but can read composer's state!
M|2.2 |tx|fn MessagePreview() {
M|2.2 |tx|const { state } = use(ComposerContext)
M|2.2 |tx|return <Preview message={state.input} attachments={state.attachments} />
M|2.2 |tx|}
M|2.2 |tx|```
M|2.2 |tx|The pr boundary is what matters—not the visual nesting. cp that
M|2.2 |tx|need shared state don't have to be inside the `Composer.Frame`. They just need
M|2.2 |tx|to be within the pr.
M|2.2 |tx|The `ForwardButton` and `MessagePreview` are not visually inside the composer
M|2.2 |tx|box, but they can still access its state and actions. This is the power of
M|2.2 |tx|lifting state into pr.
M|2.2 |tx|The UI is reusable bits you compose together. The state is dependency-injected
M|2.2 |tx|by the pr. Swap the pr, keep the UI.
M|2.3 |**Im|hi (enables state sharing outside cp boundaries)**
M|2.3 |tx|Move state management into dedicated pr cp. This allows sibling
M|2.3 |tx|cp outside the main UI to access and modify state w/o prop drilling
M|2.3 |tx|or awkward refs.
M|2.3 |**In|state trapped inside cp**
M|2.3 |tx|```tsx
M|2.3 |tx|fn ForwardMessageComposer() {
M|2.3 |tx|const [state, setState] = useState(initialState)
M|2.3 |tx|const forwardMessage = useForwardMessage()
M|2.3 |tx|return (
M|2.3 |tx|<Composer.Frame>
M|2.3 |tx|<Composer.Input />
M|2.3 |tx|<Composer.Footer />
M|2.3 |tx|</Composer.Frame>
M|2.3 |tx|)
M|2.3 |tx|}
M|2.3 |// P|How does this button access composer state?
M|2.3 |tx|fn ForwardMessageDialog() {
M|2.3 |tx|return (
M|2.3 |tx|<Dialog>
M|2.3 |tx|<ForwardMessageComposer />
M|2.3 |tx|<MessagePreview /> {/* Needs composer state */}
M|2.3 |tx|<DialogActions>
M|2.3 |tx|<CancelButton />
M|2.3 |tx|<ForwardButton /> {/* Needs to call submit */}
M|2.3 |tx|</DialogActions>
M|2.3 |tx|</Dialog>
M|2.3 |tx|)
M|2.3 |tx|}
M|2.3 |tx|```
M|2.3 |**In|useEffect to sync state up**
M|2.3 |tx|```tsx
M|2.3 |tx|fn ForwardMessageDialog() {
M|2.3 |tx|const [input, setInput] = useState('')
M|2.3 |tx|return (
M|2.3 |tx|<Dialog>
M|2.3 |tx|<ForwardMessageComposer onInputChange={setInput} />
M|2.3 |tx|<MessagePreview input={input} />
M|2.3 |tx|</Dialog>
M|2.3 |tx|)
M|2.3 |tx|}
M|2.3 |tx|fn ForwardMessageComposer({ onInputChange }) {
M|2.3 |tx|const [state, setState] = useState(initialState)
M|2.3 |tx|useEffect(() => {
M|2.3 |tx|onInputChange(state.input) // Sync on every change 😬
M|2.3 |tx|}, [state.input])
M|2.3 |tx|}
M|2.3 |tx|```
M|2.3 |**In|reading state from ref on submit**
M|2.3 |tx|```tsx
M|2.3 |tx|fn ForwardMessageDialog() {
M|2.3 |tx|const stateRef = useRef(null)
M|2.3 |tx|return (
M|2.3 |tx|<Dialog>
M|2.3 |tx|<ForwardMessageComposer stateRef={stateRef} />
M|2.3 |tx|<ForwardButton onPress={() => submit(stateRef.current)} />
M|2.3 |tx|</Dialog>
M|2.3 |tx|)
M|2.3 |tx|}
M|2.3 |tx|```
M|2.3 |**Co|state lifted to pr**
M|2.3 |tx|```tsx
M|2.3 |func|{ children: rc.ReactNode }) {
M|2.3 |tx|const [state, setState] = useState(initialState)
M|2.3 |tx|const forwardMessage = useForwardMessage()
M|2.3 |tx|const inputRef = useRef(null)
M|2.3 |tx|return (
M|2.3 |tx|<Composer.pr
M|2.3 |tx|state={state}
M|2.3 |acti|setState, submit: forwardMessage }}
M|2.3 |tx|meta={{ inputRef }}
M|2.3 |tx|>
M|2.3 |tx|{children}
M|2.3 |tx|</Composer.pr>
M|2.3 |tx|)
M|2.3 |tx|}
M|2.3 |tx|fn ForwardMessageDialog() {
M|2.3 |tx|return (
M|2.3 |tx|<ForwardMessageProvider>
M|2.3 |tx|<Dialog>
M|2.3 |tx|<ForwardMessageComposer />
M|2.3 |tx|<MessagePreview /> {/* Custom cp can access state and actions */}
M|2.3 |tx|<DialogActions>
M|2.3 |tx|<CancelButton />
M|2.3 |tx|<ForwardButton /> {/* Custom cp can access state and actions */}
M|2.3 |tx|</DialogActions>
M|2.3 |tx|</Dialog>
M|2.3 |tx|</ForwardMessageProvider>
M|2.3 |tx|)
M|2.3 |tx|}
M|2.3 |tx|fn ForwardButton() {
M|2.3 |tx|const { actions } = use(Composer.Context)
M|2.3 |tx|return <Button onPress={actions.submit}>Forward</Button>
M|2.3 |tx|}
M|2.3 |tx|```
M|2.3 |tx|The ForwardButton lives outside the Composer.Frame but still has access to the
M|2.3 |tx|submit action bc it's within the pr. Even though it's a one-off
M|2.3 |tx|cp, it can still access the composer's state and actions from outside the
M|2.3 |tx|UI itself.
M|2.3 |**Ke|** cp that need shared state don't have to be visually
M|2.3 |tx|nested inside each other—they just need to be within the same pr.
M|2.3 |tx|---
M|3. I|**Im|md**
M|3. I|tx|Specific techniques for implementing compound cp and
M|3. I|tx|context pr.
M|3.1 |**Im|md (self-documenting code, no hidden conditionals)**
M|3.1 |tx|Instead of one cp w/ many boolean props, cr explicit variant
M|3.1 |tx|cp. Each variant composes the pieces it needs. The code documents
M|3.1 |tx|itself.
M|3.1 |**In|one cp, many modes**
M|3.1 |tx|```tsx
M|3.1 |tx|// What does this cp actually render?
M|3.1 |tx|<Composer
M|3.1 |tx|isThread
M|3.1 |tx|isEditing={false}
M|3.1 |tx|channelId='abc'
M|3.1 |tx|showAttachments
M|3.1 |tx|showFormatting={false}
M|3.1 |tx|/>
M|3.1 |tx|```
M|3.1 |**Co|explicit variants**
M|3.1 |tx|```tsx
M|3.1 |tx|// Immediately clear what this renders
M|3.1 |tx|<ThreadComposer channelId="abc" />
M|3.1 |tx|// Or
M|3.1 |tx|<EditMessageComposer messageId="xyz" />
M|3.1 |tx|// Or
M|3.1 |tx|<ForwardMessageComposer messageId="123" />
M|3.1 |tx|```
M|3.1 |tx|Each implementation is unique, explicit and self-contained. Yet they can each
M|3.1 |tx|use shared parts.
M|3.1 |**Im|**
M|3.1 |tx|```tsx
M|3.1 |func|{ channelId: string }) {
M|3.1 |tx|return (
M|3.1 |tx|<ThreadProvider channelId={channelId}>
M|3.1 |tx|<Composer.Frame>
M|3.1 |tx|<Composer.Input />
M|3.1 |tx|<AlsoSendToChannelField channelId={channelId} />
M|3.1 |tx|<Composer.Footer>
M|3.1 |tx|<Composer.Formatting />
M|3.1 |tx|<Composer.Emojis />
M|3.1 |tx|<Composer.Submit />
M|3.1 |tx|</Composer.Footer>
M|3.1 |tx|</Composer.Frame>
M|3.1 |tx|</ThreadProvider>
M|3.1 |tx|)
M|3.1 |tx|}
M|3.1 |func|{ messageId: string }) {
M|3.1 |tx|return (
M|3.1 |tx|<EditMessageProvider messageId={messageId}>
M|3.1 |tx|<Composer.Frame>
M|3.1 |tx|<Composer.Input />
M|3.1 |tx|<Composer.Footer>
M|3.1 |tx|<Composer.Formatting />
M|3.1 |tx|<Composer.Emojis />
M|3.1 |tx|<Composer.CancelEdit />
M|3.1 |tx|<Composer.SaveEdit />
M|3.1 |tx|</Composer.Footer>
M|3.1 |tx|</Composer.Frame>
M|3.1 |tx|</EditMessageProvider>
M|3.1 |tx|)
M|3.1 |tx|}
M|3.1 |func|{ messageId: string }) {
M|3.1 |tx|return (
M|3.1 |tx|<ForwardMessageProvider messageId={messageId}>
M|3.1 |tx|<Composer.Frame>
M|3.1 |tx|<Composer.Input placeholder="Add a message, if you'd like." />
M|3.1 |tx|<Composer.Footer>
M|3.1 |tx|<Composer.Formatting />
M|3.1 |tx|<Composer.Emojis />
M|3.1 |tx|<Composer.Mentions />
M|3.1 |tx|</Composer.Footer>
M|3.1 |tx|</Composer.Frame>
M|3.1 |tx|</ForwardMessageProvider>
M|3.1 |tx|)
M|3.1 |tx|}
M|3.1 |tx|```
M|3.1 |Each|
M|3.1 |it|What pr/state it uses
M|3.1 |it|What UI elements it includes
M|3.1 |it|What actions are available
M|3.1 |tx|No boolean prop combinations to reason abt. No impossible states.
M|3.2 |**Im|md (cleaner composition, better readability)**
M|3.2 |tx|Use `children` for composition instead of `renderX` props. Children are more
M|3.2 |tx|readable, compose naturally, and don't require understanding callback
M|3.2 |tx|signatures.
M|3.2 |**In|render props**
M|3.2 |tx|```tsx
M|3.2 |tx|fn Composer({
M|3.2 |tx|renderHeader,
M|3.2 |tx|renderFooter,
M|3.2 |tx|renderActions,
M|3.2 |}|{
M|3.2 |rend|() => rc.ReactNode
M|3.2 |rend|() => rc.ReactNode
M|3.2 |rend|() => rc.ReactNode
M|3.2 |tx|}) {
M|3.2 |tx|return (
M|3.2 |tx|<form>
M|3.2 |tx|{renderHeader?.()}
M|3.2 |tx|<Input />
M|3.2 |{ren|<DefaultFooter />}
M|3.2 |tx|{renderActions?.()}
M|3.2 |tx|</form>
M|3.2 |tx|)
M|3.2 |tx|}
M|3.2 |tx|// Usage is awkward and inflexible
M|3.2 |tx|return (
M|3.2 |tx|<Composer
M|3.2 |tx|renderHeader={() => <CustomHeader />}
M|3.2 |tx|renderFooter={() => (
M|3.2 |tx|<>
M|3.2 |tx|<Formatting />
M|3.2 |tx|<Emojis />
M|3.2 |tx|</>
M|3.2 |tx|)}
M|3.2 |tx|renderActions={() => <SubmitButton />}
M|3.2 |tx|/>
M|3.2 |tx|)
M|3.2 |tx|```
M|3.2 |**Co|compound cp w/ children**
M|3.2 |tx|```tsx
M|3.2 |func|{ children: rc.ReactNode }) {
M|3.2 |tx|return <form>{children}</form>
M|3.2 |tx|}
M|3.2 |func|{ children: rc.ReactNode }) {
M|3.2 |tx|return <footer className='flex'>{children}</footer>
M|3.2 |tx|}
M|3.2 |tx|// Usage is flexible
M|3.2 |tx|return (
M|3.2 |tx|<Composer.Frame>
M|3.2 |tx|<CustomHeader />
M|3.2 |tx|<Composer.Input />
M|3.2 |tx|<Composer.Footer>
M|3.2 |tx|<Composer.Formatting />
M|3.2 |tx|<Composer.Emojis />
M|3.2 |tx|<SubmitButton />
M|3.2 |tx|</Composer.Footer>
M|3.2 |tx|</Composer.Frame>
M|3.2 |tx|)
M|3.2 |tx|```
M|3.2 |**Wh|**
M|3.2 |tx|```tsx
M|3.2 |tx|// Render props work well when you need to pass data back
M|3.2 |tx|<List
M|3.2 |tx|data={items}
M|3.2 |tx|renderItem={({ item, index }) => <Item item={item} index={index} />}
M|3.2 |tx|/>
M|3.2 |tx|```
M|3.2 |tx|Use render props when the parent needs to provide data or state to the child.
M|3.2 |tx|Use children when composing static structure.
M|3.2 |tx|---
M|4. R|**Im|md**
M|4. R|tx|rc 19+ only. Don't use `forwardRef`; use `use()` instead of `useContext()`.
M|4.1 |**Im|md (cleaner cp definitions and context usage)**
M|4.1 |tx|> **⚠️ rc 19+ only.** Skip this if you're on rc 18 or earlier.
M|4.1 |tx|In rc 19, `ref` is now a regular prop (no `forwardRef` wrapper needed), and `use()` replaces `useContext()`.
M|4.1 |**In|forwardRef in rc 19**
M|4.1 |tx|```tsx
M|4.1 |tx|const ComposerInput = forwardRef<TextInput, Props>((props, ref) => {
M|4.1 |tx|return <TextInput ref={ref} {...props} />
M|4.1 |tx|})
M|4.1 |tx|```
M|4.1 |**Co|ref as a regular prop**
M|4.1 |tx|```tsx
M|4.1 |func|Props & { ref?: rc.Ref<TextInput> }) {
M|4.1 |tx|return <TextInput ref={ref} {...props} />
M|4.1 |tx|}
M|4.1 |tx|```
M|4.1 |**In|useContext in rc 19**
M|4.1 |tx|```tsx
M|4.1 |tx|const value = useContext(MyContext)
M|4.1 |tx|```
M|4.1 |**Co|use instead of useContext**
M|4.1 |tx|```tsx
M|4.1 |tx|const value = use(MyContext)
M|4.1 |tx|```
M|4.1 |tx|`use()` can also be called conditionally, unlike `useContext()`.
M|4.1 |tx|---
